9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1237, L.D. 1853, “An Act to Establish
10 an Educational Tax Credit Program to Help Parents Pay for Nonpublic School Tuition and
11 Fees”
12 Amend the bill in section 2 in c. 220 in §5902 by striking out all of subsection 1 (page
13 1, lines 20 and 21 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
14 '1. Eligible student. "Eligible student" means a resident of the State who is eligible
15 to enroll in an elementary or secondary public school and is not enrolled in a nonpublic
16 school on October 1, 2025.'
17 Amend the bill in section 2 in c. 220 in §5906 in subsection 1 in paragraph C in the 4th
18 line (page 2, line 21 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "70%" and inserting the
19 following: '55%'
20 Amend the bill in section 2 in c. 220 in §5906 in subsection 1 in paragraph C in the last
21 line (page 2, line 23 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "70%" and inserting the
22 following: '55%'
23 Amend the bill in section 3 in §5217-G in subsection 1 by striking out all of paragraph
24 C (page 3, lines 1 to 3 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
25 'C. "Qualified taxpayer" means a taxpayer who:
26 (1) Is a resident of the State;
27 (2) Files a state income tax return;
28 (3) Is not a dependent of another taxpayer; and
29 (4) Is the parent or guardian of a student who meets the requirements of Title 20-A,
30 section 5904.'
31 Amend the bill in section 3 in §5217-G by striking out all of subsection 2 (page 3, lines
32 6 to 12 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
33 '2. Credit allowed. For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, a qualified
34 taxpayer is allowed a credit against the tax imposed by this Part in accordance with the
