26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment specifies that to qualify for the education tax credit under the bill, the
2288 taxpayer must be a resident of Maine and the eligible student must be a resident of Maine
2299 who is not enrolled in a nonpublic school on October 1, 2025. The amendment decreases
3300 the maximum credit from 70% to 55% of the cost of publicly funded education, requires
3311 the State Tax Assessor to annually determine the maximum credit that is available for each
3322 eligible student and specifies that the credit may not exceed the cost of tuition and fees paid
3333 by the taxpayer.
3344 The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
